>
  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6 italic text-gray-300">Four-player co-op Legendary run of Halo 3 on MCC, completed in approximately two hours. The group plays efficiently and speed-runs most missions, collecting skulls and chasing par times throughout.</p>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">General Notes</h2>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Halo 3 Legendary is considered the easiest of the mainline games when played with four experienced players — enemies don't meaningfully scale for the extra firepower.</li>
    <li>Halo 4 is considered harder due to Promethean Watchers (which intercept grenades) and the Binary Rifle.</li>
    <li>Par times are 15 minutes per mission for most levels. Scoring must be turned on before the mission to count toward par score achievements.</li>
    <li>Terminals in Halo 3 require reading all pages to unlock achievements — just activating them is not enough. All players must be present.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Do not destroy the Phantom</strong> on early missions — it will glitch the mission if destroyed.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">Sierra 117</h2>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>The <strong class="text-cyan-400">Bandana Skull</strong> is available at the start — grab it for infinite ammo.</li>
    <li>There's an achievement for <strong class="text-cyan-400">looking at the monkeys</strong> (Grunt birthday party-style easter egg up on the cliffs).</li>
    <li>A stationary <strong class="text-cyan-400">turret</strong> near the bug/Drone section makes clearing it trivially easy.</li>
    <li>The brute encounter near the end is the hardest part of this mission. Removing brute helmets with gunfire exposes their heads.</li>
    <li>Healing brutes (in a Bubble Shield) still take damage — just overwhelm them.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">Crow's Nest</h2>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>The bomb objective requires players to arm it and exit — the door sequence can be tricky with four people.</li>
    <li>You can skip fighting many enemies and just sprint to objectives.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">Tsavo Highway</h2>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Do not destroy the Phantom</strong> — confirmed to glitch the mission in MCC.</li>
    <li>Warthog driving is the focus; one gunner on the turret makes clearing the highway fast.</li>
    <li>Ghost choppers appear on the highway and can be hijacked.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">The Storm</h2>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>The anti-air Wraith on the island must be destroyed to progress.</li>
    <li>You <strong class="text-cyan-400">do not have to kill the Hunters</strong> in the tunnel — you can walk past them.</li>
    <li>The in-engine moment where the UNSC ship comes in low and its shockwave sends enemies flying is one of the most impressive set pieces in all of gaming — not a cutscene.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">The Ark</h2>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">"Tank Beats Everything" achievement</strong>: Use the Scorpion tank to kill Hunters, Ghosts, and then destroy the Phantom. The NPC Marine will say the line when all three are done.</li>
    <li>The tank is lost after the indoor section — enjoy it while it lasts.</li>
    <li>Terminals on this level require all pages read for achievement credit.</li>
    <li>The <strong class="text-cyan-400">"Used Car Salesman" achievement</strong> requires killing three enemies in a single vehicle simultaneously.</li>
    <li>Hornets are available in the open section; grabbing them early makes the Scarab sequence much easier.</li>
    <li>The Scarab fight: shooting the glowing joints/lights with missile pods brings it down. Players can board it directly.</li>
    <li>Two Scarabs appear near the end.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">The Covenant</h2>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Three-tower mission. Each tower must be activated in sequence.</li>
    <li>You can run past most waves — they do not need to be cleared to progress.</li>
    <li>Do not kill Johnson — he is needed for a later sequence involving the weapon.</li>
    <li>Guilty Spark turns on the team here and kills Johnson; this is unavoidable story progression.</li>
    <li>All four players must be present at terminals for the achievement to trigger.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">Cortana</h2>

  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">Set inside High Charity — heavily Flood-infested.</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>This mission is widely considered the most annoying in the game due to the Gravemind voice repeatedly interrupting.</li>
    <li>Running ahead of enemies is the most effective strategy — Flood enemies have to transform/spawn in, so staying ahead of spawn triggers keeps the path clear.</li>
    <li>Grenades must be placed on specific platforms to proceed. You need at least one grenade.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">Halo (Final Mission)</h2>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Ghost/Mongoose achievement</strong>: All players must complete the final escape sequence in Ghosts or Mongooses — high lag risk in co-op.</li>
    <li>The par time for the Warthog run is very tight — speed run from the moment the sequence begins.</li>
    <li>There is a boomer-type Flood enemy near the end of the escape that can one-shot vehicles — keep moving.</li>
    <li>The full campaign run clocked in just over 2 hours.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">Achievement Notes</h2>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Par Times</strong>: 15 minutes per mission on most levels. Scoring must be enabled before starting the mission.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Tank Beats Everything</strong> (The Ark): Kill Hunters, Ghosts, and Phantom with the Scorpion.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Monkey achievement</strong> (Sierra 117): Look at / interact with all the Grunts on the cliffs.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Skull collection</strong>: Gold skulls only count toward the main skull achievement; silver skulls do not.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Terminal achievement</strong>: All players must be present; all pages must be read.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Ghost/Mongoose escape</strong> (Halo): All players must finish in a Ghost or Mongoose — high lag risk in co-op.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Legendary in under 3 hours</strong>: Achievable with four experienced players; the group finished around 2 hours.</li>
  </ul>
